&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Galvanize’s&amp;nbsp;Investor Partnerships team leads fundraising and investor relations across asset classes.&amp;nbsp;The&amp;nbsp;Investor Partnerships&amp;nbsp;Team develops,&amp;nbsp;maintains, and&amp;nbsp;grows&amp;nbsp;relationships with prospective and current Limited Partners (“LP’s”’, investors, or allocators) globally on behalf of the firm.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The incumbent will report directly to the Global Head of Credit Capital Formation and will primarily service the Galvanize Credit and Capital Solutions team. This role is an outstanding opportunity for an individual wanting to expand their knowledge of energy-transition-focused investments and the fundraising and relationship management function of a growing, multi-asset investment platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:278}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Candidate must have at least 2 years of experience in private credit.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;36&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&qu

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Galvanize&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Galvanize is a global asset manager investing at the intersection of energy innovation, resilience, and intelligence. The firm deploys capital across seed, venture, growth, public equities, credit, and real estate, combining investment expertise with deep in-house capabilities in technology, policy, and markets. Galvanize is structured to rapidly identify and execute on investment opportunities created by the energy transition, across all sectors of the economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Strategy Associate sits within the Galvanize Platform and plays a central role in advancing the firm’s investment capabilities and strategic growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a high-impact, cross-functional role working closely with investment teams and senior leadership. The Associate develops cross-asset insights, supports firm-wide strategic initiatives, and engages externally with leaders across climate, industry, and finance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The role blends analytical rigor with ecosystem engagement and execution. You will generate market insights to inform investment decisions, activate a global network of partners, and design high-impact convenings that shape dialogue across the energy transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strategy Initiatives &amp;amp; Research&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop high-quality materials to support firm-wide strategic initiatives, partnerships, and growth efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct targeted deep dives on priority themes (e.g., cross-firm investable opportunities across the nuclear supply chain, climate physical risk, or carbon markets)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce market maps, thematic analyses, and internal briefings that inform investment and partnership decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize insights across teams and asset classes into clear, actionable outputs for internal and external audiences&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Network Development &amp;amp; Value Creation&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage and activate Galvanize’s global network, including corporates, investors, NGOs, and industry bodies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture insights from network interactions and translate them into actionable inputs for investment teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive follow-ups, introductions, and relationship development across key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support portfolio companies through strategic introductions, partnerships, and go-to-market efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to external initiatives (e.g., working groups, partnerships), with the opportunity to represent Galvanize over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Convening Strategy&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute strategic convenings (e.g., roundtables, executive dinners) that bring together senior leaders across climate, industry, and finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive key components of the Galvanize Solutions Summit, including content strategy and partner engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture and synthesize insights from convenings to inform firm strategy and investment activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong alignment with Galvanize’s mission to accelerate and scale climate solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of experience in consulting, investing, partnerships, or a high-growth operating environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical and synthesis skills, with the ability to distill complex market, policy, and business information into clear insights and actionab

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Galvanize Climate Solutions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Galvanize is a global asset manager investing at the intersection of energy innovation, resilience, and intelligence. The firm deploys capital across seed, venture, growth, public equities, credit, and real estate, combining investment expertise with deep in-house&amp;nbsp;capabilities in technology, policy, and markets. Galvanize is structured to rapidly identify and execute on investment opportunities created by the energy transition, across all sectors of the economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Investment Associate will be a core member of Galvanize’s Venture and Growth team. This role sits at the center of our effort to build scaled, category-defining companies that power the next era of energy and climate. Associates are active participants in theme development, investment execution, and portfolio value creation. The role offers exposure to the full investment lifecycle: from identifying structural shifts across electrification, intelligence, and industrial systems, to underwriting companies positioned to lead those shifts, to supporting management teams as they scale. Our Venture and Growth strategy provides capital to commercially validated businesses with strong leadership, differentiated technology, and clear pathways to profitability. We focus on companies ready to move from product-market fit to scaled deployment in the real economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key investment themes include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;Electrification and the scaling of intelligence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;Data, digitization, and controls for the new economy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Firm and flexible power generation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Industrial efficiency and automation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sustainable inputs, resources, and supply chains&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;System resilience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are long-term partners to our portfolio companies, working alongside founders and executives to accelerate commercialization, navigate policy and market complexity, and build durable category leadership.&amp;nbsp;This role is well-suited for an intellectually curious, execution-oriented investor who wants meaningful responsibility, close collaboration with senior partners, and exposure to building a differentiated climate-focused investment platform from the inside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential job responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities of the Associate will revolve around three primary types of work:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New and Follow-On Investments&lt;/strong&gt;– The Galvanize Investment Associate will play a central role in sourcing, evaluating, and executing new and follow-on investments across the portfolio. This includes proactive thematic research, market mapping, relationship development with founders and ecosystem partners, market analysis, financial modeling, and preparation of investment committee materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Portfolio Management&lt;/strong&gt;– The Galvanize Investment Associate will support portfolio company reporting, performance tracking, and valuation analysis. The Associate will also work with portfolio companies on select strategic and operational initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fund Administration&lt;/strong&gt;– The Galvanize Investment Associate will assist with fund reporting, valuation support, data collection, and external events such as annual investor meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
